Embedded_text: Congress heeded my calls to fund gun violence prevention research–dedicating $100M over the last 4 years. Now that research is having an impact. We must build on this and pass my Gun Violence Prevention Research Act. We can and will end gun violence.

I'm so glad that we just confirmed Julia Kobick as U.S. District Judge for Massachusetts. Our 150th judge confirmed under this Administration and an important reminder of the work ahead to protect our essential rights at all levels of the judiciary.

Yesterday, I introduced the Paraprofessionals and Education Support Staff Bill of Rights. Because from bus drivers, to custodians, to instruction assistants we need to make sure these essential workers have the dignity, respect, and recognition they have long deserved.

I was proud to host today's forum between the Senate Climate Change Task Force and the House Sustainable Energy and Environment Coalition to spotlight transmission policies that will supercharge the green energy revolution. It's time to deliver clean power to the people.

Enough is enough. As opioid deaths reach a record high, we can't keep lifesaving medication out of the hands of people who need it. We need to pass my Modernizing Opioid Treatment Access Act and let doctors prescribe methadone for SUD.

Embedded_text: Today and every day we honor our veterans for their dedication and service. This Veteran’s Day we don’t just just need to prevent a shutdown and secure their benefits—we need to keep pushing to make sure all veterans have the support and protections they need.

The climate crisis is threatening every corner of our country and the risks have never been clearer. We must lead the world in a global Green New Deal, keep up the fight for a livable future, and leave behind dirty fossil fuels. https://cnn.com/2023/11/14/us/national-climate-assessment-extreme-weather-costs/index.html…
